M: Dinner at a local restaurant (approx. \u20b9500 per person)\\n* 9:00 PM: Explore the night market at Baga Beach (free entry)\\n\\n**Day 2:**\\n\\n* 9:00 AM: Breakfast at hotel\\n* 10:00 AM: Visit Old Goa (free entry)\\n* 12:30 PM: Lunch at a local restaurant (approx. \u20b9500 per person)\\n* 2:30 PM: Water sports at Baga Beach (approx. \u20b91,500 per person)\\n* 5:00 PM: Visit Anjuna Beach (free entry)\\n* 7:30 PM: Farewell dinner at a local restaurant (approx. \u20b9500 per person)\\n* 9:30 PM: Departure from Goa\\n\\n**Budget Breakdown:**\\n\\n* Accommodation (1 night): \u20b95,711 - \u20b910,000 (including taxes and fees)\\n* Food (2 days): \u20b98,000 (approx. \u20b92,000 per meal)\\n* Transport (airport transfers, local travel): \u20b94,000\\n* Attractions: \u20b91,600 (entry fees, water sports)\\n* Total: \u20b919,311 - \u20b923,600\\n\\nPlease let me know if you have any further questions or if there's anything else I can help you with.\\n\\nAlso, I would like to know if you want to book the hotel or if you need any further assistance with the itinerary. \\n\\nAdditionally, I can provide you with more information about the hotel, such as:\\n\\n* Room types: Lemon Tree Hotel Candolim Goa offers 34 air-conditioned accommodations with minibars and safes.\\n* Amenities: The hotel features an outdoor swimming pool, free WiFi, and a great dining spot.\\n* Location: The hotel is located in the heart of North Goa, a 10-minute drive from Fort Aguada, and close to Calangute Beach and Baga Beach.\\n\\nPlease let me know if you need any further information or assistance.\\n\\nThe hotel has received positive reviews from guests, with an overall rating of 7.8. Guests have praised the hotel's excellent service, comfortable accommodations, and convenient location.\\n\\nSome of the reviews mention:\\n\\n* \\\"Humble and polite staff, thanks to Sanyukta at front desk and Yogesh at restaurant.\\\"\\n* \\\"Neat and clean rooms, quick housekeeping services\\\"\\n* \\\"The st